---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy — Habit Build" description="Your privacy matters. Here's how Habit Build handles your data.">
  <Nav currentPage="home" />

  <main class="flex-1">
    <div class="max-w-[600px] mx-auto px-4 md:px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
      <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-[-1.28px] text-ink mb-8">Privacy</h1>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-sm text-body leading-relaxed">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-ink mb-2">Data Stays on Your Device</h2>
          <p>Habit Build stores all your data locally in your browser using localStorage. No data is ever sent to a server, logged, or shared with anyone.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-ink mb-2">No Account Required</h2>
          <p>You don't need to create an account or provide any personal information to use Habit Build. There are no sign-ups, no emails, and no passwords.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-ink mb-2">No Tracking</h2>
          <p>Habit Build does not use analytics, cookies, or tracking scripts. Your habit data and usage patterns remain private to you.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-ink mb-2">Clearing Your Data</h2>
          <p>You can clear all stored data at any time by clearing your browser's localStorage for this site. No residual data is kept elsewhere.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-ink mb-2">Third Parties</h2>
          <p>Habit Build does not integrate with any third-party services, APIs, or data processors. The app is fully self-contained in your browser.</p>
        </section>

        <p class="text-xs text-mute pt-4 border-t border-hairline">Last updated: June 2026</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
